                    DHSP    Mail Code  (726)    Office Hours  By appointment    Related Sites  Assistive Technology Certificate Program   Assistive Technology Unit     About  Jennifer is the fieldwork coordinator for the Assistive Technology Certificate Program (ATCP) and visiting clinical instructor.  She has worked in the field of assistive technology for over 20 years working with adults and students.  In her 20 years she has worked at Northwest Suburban Special Education Cooperative, Lockport Area Special Education Cooperative, the UIC Assistive Technology Unit, and United Cerebral Palsy/Infinitec.  Her passion is promoting independence for individuals with disabilities through the use of technology.     Education  Master of Science, Disability and Human Development, University of Illinois at Chicago, 2001 Bachelor of Science, Communication Disorders & Sciences, Eastern Illinois University, 1997           Disability and Human Development    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          Minor in Disability and Human Development    BS in Disability and Human Development    Expand BS in Disability and Human Development menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      MS in Disability and Human Development    PhD in Disability Studies    Expand PhD in Disability Studies menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty    Meet Our Students      Assistive Technology Certificate    Expand Assistive Technology Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying    Faculty    Assistive Technology Certificate FAQ      Disability Ethics Certificate    Expand Disability Ethics Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying        Institute on Disability and Human Development    Community Partners    Expand Community Partners menu          Bodies of Work      Rese